<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Backup Recovery Codes</h1>

  <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 text-yellow-800 px-4 py-3 rounded mb-6">
    <strong>Important:</strong> Save these codes in a safe place. Each code can only be used once.
    You'll need these codes to access your account if you lose your phone or can't receive verification codes.
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Your backup codes:</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded font-mono">
      <% @backup_codes.each do |code| %>
        <div class="text-lg"><%= code %></div>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <p>✓ Store these codes somewhere safe (password manager, printed copy, etc.)</p>
      <p>✓ Each code can only be used once</p>
      <p>✓ You can generate new codes at any time (old codes will be invalidated)</p>
      <p>✓ Use these codes if you can't access your authenticator app or phone</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t">
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
        <button onclick="window.print()" class="bg-gray-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-700 transition">
          Print Codes
        </button>
        <%= link_to "I've Saved My Codes", account_path,
                    class: "bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6 text-center text-sm text-gray-600">
    <p>You can regenerate new backup codes at any time from your account settings.</p>
    <p>Doing so will invalidate all previous backup codes.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<style media="print">
  body * {
    visibility: hidden;
  }
  .grid.grid-cols-2, .grid.grid-cols-2 * {
    visibility: visible;
  }
  .grid.grid-cols-2 {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
  }
</style>